I literally can’t run… there’s snow outside with ice on top of it which makes it difficult to even walk, I don’t even want to try to drive in it. The gym is closed. I don’t own a treadmill. So we were constrained to house activities which ended up being pretty difficult but still not the same as 17 miles… I might try my track spikes unironically tomorrow.

Alize said it doesn’t snow here and that’s most of the reason I moved here… but it wasn’t too bad. There was like an inch on ground which made it difficult to run but we pulled out the trail shoes 😤 and it ended up kind of fun!

Activity Name: When you realize mid double that you’re on track for 110 miles and could’ve not doubled
Description: Alize and I went pretty easy on my double (her single) which was nice. My body did not want to go any faster! I’m not really sore but definitely tired.

15:30 (5:10), 15:12 (5:04), 14:59 (4:59), 14:41 (4:53). For my route I would do 2 peppertree loops -> 2 Pam loops -> ~2 peppertree loops. Between the loops the GPS is off because going to the Pam loop and back I was in the exact same location… looks like I was across the street on the map? Today was a mixed bag. I felt pretty good for the first 2 miles of each rep but the third was always the hardest. I’d be well under pace through 2 and then hardly hit pace the last mile. And 3 miles at 4:54 pace should not feel as uncomfortable as it did today… it was still a solid workout but pretty difficult and I’m definitely going to need to recover well. I had an orange gel at the beginning of rep 2 but I think I was dehydrated, I didn’t drink any water this morning at all (I didn’t really notice but I’m sure it affected me). Almost got hit with like 0.25 miles to go on the last one… The weather was nearly perfect, it didn’t rain much at all and the wind chill wasn’t as bad as the weather app said.
I’ve got to get a video of the geese one of these days…

Activity Name: Just because you can make a loop doesn’t mean you should
Description: Not the best loop for tonight but that’s okay! I was really delaying this run, I didn’t feel like doubling at all for some reason. I felt okay but it was dark and rainy and I had a long day.

I’m honestly starting to enjoy this route even more, especially with such great company 😉 Alize Hartke . It was like 30 with wind chill so I wore the balaclava for the first time and absolutely loved it! I felt great today. I tried 2 pieces of pb toast and 8 oz of water before the run and it didn’t bother me at all.

I went to a neighborhood that I hadn't been to yet which was fun. It's pancake flat and not very busy. The rest of the run was pretty boring and dragged on. I didn't feel like running any faster than average until like the last mile which was kind of funny.

1:56.4, 1:55.4, 1:55.2, 1:53.5, 1:54.2, 1:53.0, 1:55.1, 1:54.0, 1:55.0, 1:54.8, 1:54.7, 1:54.3, 1:54.7, 1:54.1, 1:53.8. This workout was unique but I liked it. The weather was actually really good for the evening session, just a little cold. Usually I don’t feel this good in the evening so honestly couldn’t have asked for more!
There were so many geese near Churchill is was insane… luckily didn’t come home with any battle scars

3:15, 3:16, 3:17, 3:14, 3:17, 3:13, 3:13, 3:14, 3:13, 3:15. The 1k loop was around 4-5 seconds more than what it should’ve been. It was rainy and windy intermittently today so I decided to do this neighborhood loop instead of the track since the track has no coverage and was SUPER windy. The workout today basically felt like an easy run, 5:00-5:10 feels way easier since that 400s workout on Saturday. I was worried I wouldn’t be warm enough but even the first rep felt really good! Couldn’t have asked for a better morning despite the weather being so weird!

6x15” strides. My headlamp was getting low on battery so I couldn’t see much this run. That didn’t stop me from running the uneven and very dark bark loop by our house because my body needed some soft surface. I felt okay but I was glad to be done at the end. The strides were not great, very slow and didn’t feel like strides at all.
I felt meh today, not bad though. Just after an asphalt long run I never feel all that great.

Alize and I did around 6.5 at the reservoir (0.27 mile loop) and then I finished going down the big hill and Alize picked me up there so I had a net downhill today 😂. I felt good! This didn’t get boring at all and was actually really nice.

Averaged 5:10, 5:10, 5:00, 5:08, 5:12. Today was a marathon simulation day so I tried to do everything that I would do on race day, including dinner last night. I took a gel right before and then a gel at around 5 miles and another gel around 11 miles. I also had some electrolyte mix at around miles 3, 7, and after the workout during the cooldown. 11 miles of work at race pace with fueling was just what I needed! Definitely got a lot of confidence from that one. Most reps felt very comfortable despite my janky bottle setup and loop.
The 8 strides on the track felt pretty good.
I went out to the little commercial loop out there and it is a really good spot to workout. We’ll definitely have to come back here at some point.

Alize said I was going too slow this morning with her so I had to show her my easy run pace is the same 😤. I did not feel good this evening, but it’s nothing too bad. Just a little soreness and fatigue maybe from the treadmill workout yesterday.

Ran most of this with Alize and then did a loop afterwards. There were lots of police and electric people on the more rural roads which made it a little busier than normal. I felt decent but I’m definitely tired from last night’s workout

Activity Name: 4x(1 mile, 0.75 mile, 0.5 mile w/ 1’ jog) w/ 2’ jog
Description: Paces were: 5:15, 5:07, 5:00 for the miles, 3/4 miles, and half miles. All on the treadmill today. The first few reps were not that comfortable but after 12 they started to get pretty comfortable 🤪. Still too icy to workout outside but we did try. I had Alex  Helmuth  as company which was way better than running solo on a tready forever. At the end of the day it was a long workout and I feel like I executed well despite the hot humid conditions in Alex’s apartment gym.

Activity Name: Dragonflies out to 18th and then speedgoats for the middle miles and then back to the dragonflies again.
Description: Our street is still icy in some parts and very unpredictable so I wore spikes to get out of here. The run was good, I had to stick to busy roads and try to find as much ground as I could. No close calls with ice! Hopefully it’ll be gone very soon.

Alex did 8 which kept me going for a while. I cranked down to around 5:52 or something but then went back to 6:30-7:00 for the last two. The ice outside is sooo dangerous :(. I have to wear my dragonflies whenever I go outside. I’ve already slipped and Alex had a few issues when driving that I’ll keep to myself 😂

The only parts I didn’t really run were the first mile and the little turn around that goes south. Overall this is an awesome course. It was pretty windy which was a little concerning and the uphill might get me on the third lap but other than that it’s perfect. After the first mile I felt like I was dehydrated but once I got going I felt good!

Just explored around the air bnb tonight. I found a track that is impossible to get to and a few neighborhood loops that would be good for workouts. I’m not really seeing any soft surfaces but maybe I’ll find some later. Saw some cockroaches at a stoplight 😒

10:32, 1:47.6, 1:48.9, 1:50.1, 1:49.3, 1:48.6, 1:50.1, 1:47.9, 1:49.1, 1:49.0, 1:49.4. My body was really confused about running faster than 75s at first but after 4 the 600s felt comfortable. I definitely had some fun out there although I was trying to avoid the puddles on the track… last workout before I head to Orlando tomorrow!

6x100m strides w/ 100 jog. I enjoyed the run today and we did a loop that we had only ever driven before which was fun. It was hilly as heck but I was running slower so I didn’t mind. The strides were okay but right now I only have 2 speeds when striding: sprinting or mile pace. Nothing in between.

I actually ran earlier than normal today which was really nice. I’ve been wanting to get back into a better schedule so hopefully I will after the trials. It’s so nice and quiet and beautiful early in the morning, I miss it.

I did Alize’s workout and then finished up a few extra miles to hit 10. I felt good today, it’s interesting hope much I enjoy doing Alize’s workouts, it’s fun without being difficult. I enjoyed it. The weather couldn’t make up its mind but hey at least I got a rainbow out of it!
Just did a 2 mile loop and 2.5 miles of turf loops. It was a little colder than I thought and I got going pretty late but it was still a nice run.

3:42, 53, 3:43, 46, 3:45, 48, 3:49, 46, 3:48, 48, 3:48, 46, 3:48, 47, 3:46, 46. This workout felt really good! The goal was slightly faster than marathon pace and I grabbed bottles every rep either 800m or 600m in depending on where I started. I went out a little hot but eventually settled in to 3:48s which was perfect. The float actually was nice, somehow I would be rested and ready to go after the float every time. This was definitely some great practice and a great confidence builder!

8x100m strides. Usually I do strides after the run but today I worked them in the middle. The strides felt really good mechanically, but I also felt like I was dehydrated or didn’t eat enough. Overall some very solid strides though. I’m starting to feel fresher and fresher.

I went to go check out the disc golf area to see if it was still runnable and some of it is but there are a lot of puddles around. Then I ran on the path a bit and ended up making a loop. I felt solid, nothing special.
Started pretty easy and slowly progressed a little bit. It was hard for me to really want to go faster on the bark so I didn’t really. Still it felt good to get a few quicker miles on the legs.

I went out 2.5 miles and by the time I got back I was at slightly under 5 so not sure what happened but oh well. I felt decent, running is definitely starting to feel natural again. Alize was a little too slow for me today so this was mostly on my own.

Not sure how accurate the bike was but I was doing like 400 W for the first 6 minute ons and then the last four were like 250-300 since I was getting tired lol. Offs were around 120 watts. The bike display was human powered and I slowed down once and it turned off so I don’t have an official distance 🤷‍♂️

I basically did 3 miles and then 2.5 ish while filming Alize’s workout and then ran back home. I had fun honestly and I’m gonna make a fire video 🔥. I felt good today, I’m glad I got all that soft surface running on the turf. There weren’t as many geese as normal, but this is what I refer to as “Goosepocalypse”.

It felt like I wasn't even running today because it was so natural. I think that's a good sign on only day 3 of running. I ran to the short bark loop which had some caution tape blocking it but I couldn't figure out why so I just did a few loops and dipped anyways... It was pretty rainy today and a little cold but I had tights and a jacket so it wasn't too bad. I'm really looking forward to this season!
I felt a lot better today than yesterday! Running actually felt natural and good. It said it was 32° when we left but it definitely did not feel that cold.

Activity Name: Legs have not recovered since the marathon…
Description: The ground felt super heavy today, I had to do stretches like 3 minutes in… I definitely wasn’t expecting to feel this slow but that’s okay. My legs were just not responding. Everything else felt decent.

I ran with Zay for the first 4 miles and then ran by myself for the rest. I went a little further than expected and wanted to keep going at the end which was a nice surprise! I felt good today and I stuck to the bark in hopes that it’ll make me feel even better this coming week. My first workout will be on Friday which should be fun :).
I ran with Alize on and off. I stuck to the flat loops and then did one more half Churchill loop at the end. I felt good and it was really nice out there!

Normal warmup,
4 sets:
10 dumbbell dead lift 35 lb
10 weight bar row 60 lb

1 set:
10 pushups
2’ bicycle

The WU and cooldown were level 15 which was about 200W and the ons were around 270-310W (lvl 18) and the offs were around 120W (lvl 10) I’m getting a sense for the wattage on these things and it seems like the only thing that is consistent.

4 strides. The first two were warming up then the second two were pretty much all out while trying to remain relaxed. The run went well today. I still feel unfit or something but I guess it’s week two. I can’t wait to actually do a workout though!

I kept delaying this and ended up running pretty late and between meetings. It was nowhere near as fun running today as yesterday but it wasn’t too bad. I felt good but somehow I don’t feel fit and I want to workout already.

Got to run on Hayward today although it was super early. Alize absolutely smashed her workout, maybe a little too much on the last rep. Mainly just jogged on the outer lanes with Alex the whole way and helped with lactate testing here and there.
Easy 45”, small gym sesh afterwards. I felt good. I think level 15 the whole way so like 200-250W

Alize’s workout was 1 mile, 3 mile, 1 mile so I ran it with her and her workout group. I tried the Hyperion elites to see what they were made of and I definitely liked them but it’s hard to tell how good they will be. After today I’d be comfortable wearing them in a workout of my own.

At 5.5 I switched to my new endorphin speed, ran the 0.7 to the track to do 4 100m strides and then ran back home. I felt decent today, my back hurt a ton yesterday but it feels a lot better today but it still meant some conservative strides.

I forgot about the time change so it was a little rough to get going. The weather was also horrible. It was supposed to be 45+ to start and a percent chance of rain but instead it was 41° when I ended and it never stopped raining the entire run. Not to mention the moderate winds, wind chill, and rain chill. Got super muddy and could hardly feel my legs but I still enjoyed it since Alex  Helmuth  was with me most of the way. Just barely made it to 70 miles this week, my body has been enjoying the lower mileage during the build up more so than usual.

I felt really good this evening. It was a mixture of perfect weather, a place I don’t run too much, good fuel, and my body feeling good. If I felt like this during every run I would WAMT to run 100+ miles a week.
Went out to Lane to watch Alize get 2nd in the 1500 at Lane. I had a really great time cheering her on but I didn’t get as many miles as I had hoped. The trails around here are pretty nice.

Activity Name: 4x(1’, 2’, 3’) w/ half of previous rep rest + 20’ CD
Description: Average pace for the 1’, 2’, and 3’ reps: 4:49, 5:03, 5:20; 4:49, 5:15, 5:03; 4:42, 5:06, 5:13; 4:42, 5:16, 5:13. The 2’ rep was always hard since the 1’ reps were fast and had short rest after them. Sometimes it was hard, other times it was easy, and it wasn’t super consistent since the first part of the loop is slow. Accidentally got my cooldown in here too but oh well. My body is really fresh which is super nice, I hope I feel like this for most of the track season.
Warmed up around 3.5 and then did 4xmile at 6:15ish. Then cooled down on the turf fields. I love doing this and might continue, it’s just so easy to get 10 miles in when it’s not boring.
Went up to the reservoir and ran some laps. It was a little muddy but not too bad at all. I felt solid but I also felt the workout from this morning a tiny bit.

Ran in the JB 9000s today (John Bennett) and I liked them a lot. The workout was really easy and I averaged around 5:10 for the ons. I just went out on fern ridge path and then back the same way. The first few were kind of a shock to the system but eventually they felt really comfortable and I started going faster. Had to hold back on the last one.

I was planning on a little quicker today but Alex had to drop out because he was sick so I ended up running with Zay. It was a good time except for the end where it literally felt like a bee was stinging my upper thigh every time I tried to pick it up. I tried to tell myself it was just pain and deal with it but it literally forced me to stop on several occasions. I couldn’t see anything there but I assume hair was getting stuck or some sort of chafing/bite/sting.

Activity Name: Fun Beaverton run before heading back home
Description: Alize and I really enjoyed this one, the routes around here are super cool and the gravel bike loop could be used for a workout. Someone was working out on it today. Being in the area for 24 hours has got us thinking maybe it would be fun to move here!

Activity Name: Walking around the bike track (in adidas)

Description: 2 mi T at 10:30 then 8x300 w/ 90” walk. 46.8, 45.5, 46.5, 46.7, 46.3, 46.3, 44.9, 45.9. Vaporflys for the 2 mile and then dragonflys for the 300s. This would not have been possible without Gilbert Grundy. I keep going back and forth on how I felt. My form was actually really smooth and I wasn’t straining but after 150 I would start feeling the lactate and with 50 to go I was struggling to keep the recovery swing as high as it should be because my legs were so lactic. They felt good and I know that’s a pace I can run for 1500 but I’m simply not fit enough to do it right now.

Had to get in 8 miles in 1 hour which isn’t the worst but there were some lights and stuff so I did have to rush a little bit. I felt okay but definitely not as good as Tuesday. Hoping the workout tomorrow feels good despite the longer evening run today and evening weights.
Alize somehow convinced me to do my longer run later so I went short and easy this morning. I ran to our tiny bark loop until it was time to head back.

I ran a little more than 3 miles before the meetup and then 7 ish with Zay (including about a mile with the rebel v4) and then finished the rest on my own. I felt good, it’s so much easier running with other people. I liked the rebel but I don’t think I would buy it. It feels like there is no plate whatsoever and the arch is a little high. Feels similar to a mach. Light and cloudy but not super fast and not for easy days.

The first two reps were with Ethan and Jack and the rest were solo. It was great having people to run with, Zay and I went to Big Timber practice today. I averaged 5:16, 5:06, 5:00, 4:59, 4:03, 4:01, 3:53 for the 2x10’, 2x5’, and 3x150m. I felt awesome today. Maybe it was because of the great weather, great company, maybe because it was an afternoon workout, maybe because my body feels fresh, not really sure but I love it.
Nice lil double this morning before big timber practice later today.

Location: Dorris Ranch Living History Farm, USA

Description: Thought I saw a cool birb but apparently it’s just a common pheasant
My breathing and form felt so controlled it didn’t even feel like I was running… The only thing that didn’t feel great was my calves, they were fatigued/burning after halfway for whatever reason.

Warmup (10 reps each) - Glute Bridge, Single Leg Glute Bridge, RDL, Squat , Single Leg Balance (30 seconds each leg)

Main ( 3 sets x 10 reps) - DB Squat, DB Row, DB Backwards Lunge all w/ 40lb dumbbell 

Cooldown - 2 x 10 push-ups, 2 x 10 fire hydrants, 1’ crunches, 1’ bicycles, 1’ penguins

5:17, 5:08, 5:09, 5:07, 5:00, 5:02; 21.7, 22.0, 21.3, 21.3. Alex  Helmuth had a continuous tempo so I lead the first mile, rested while he kept going for a lap, then took another mile, and continued that until I finished my 6th mile.
Ran on the earlier side with Gilbert today since I had to drop Alize off at 7am at the Zenith. I had a really good time out there and the weather was nice for us :)

We had some obstacles along the way but got a good lil progression in and really enjoyed the morning! I felt good the whole way and tried to grind a few miles at the end. It had been almost half a year since we went out here and it was just as nice as I remember.

Activity Name: Sometimes 4 mile doubles just feel SO GOOD

Description: Ran with Alex the whole way which made the run fly by.

31.2, 31.7, 61.9; 32.1, 30.7, 60.6; 31.2, 30.5, 60.8; 30.9, 29.8, 60.9. I think this would’ve been a little easier with a group of people but it was entirely solo today. I was really straining on the last 100m of the 400 rep every time. This was a really difficult workout for me but I think it’s what I need to revive myself after the marathon.

Activity Name: This run made me want to move
Description: I decided to run from the planet fitness instead of on the treadmill today. I felt pretty bad to start. The first mile or so was annoying because there was no sidewalk or shoulder. After that I went through the disc golf course and ended up eating like 3 bugs and getting a few in my eyes. Then I went back on the fern ridge path and lost count of how many homeless people I saw. I’ll probably just stick to the treadmill next time because there’s no good spots to run from the gym.

Activity Name: 1600, 2’ jog, 5 mile tempo, 2’ jog, 1600, 2’ jog, 4x150m w/ 250 jog
Description: 4:57, 5:15 avg (watch) for the 5 mile, 4:47.5, 20.8, 20.7, 20.9, 20.9. I felt surprisingly good today! The miles were the best part but honestly the 5 mile tempo on the bark was pretty hard! My legs handled it fine but I couldn’t catch my breath. Then on the 150s I was just hitting a terminal velocity and couldn’t seem to go any faster. Overall today was awesome and it definitely made me rethink a few things. It feels weird for a workout to actually be hard but it brought me back to some of my college workouts. Definitely a good one out there.

Sometimes it’s fun to just bring my phone on the run so I can play music, explore new areas, and route myself back home. I really enjoyed the run today even though I felt like a crippled tortoise at the start.
68.5, 66.3, 66.3, 65.0, 65.7, 64.9, 64.7, 64.7. I actually felt pretty good post race. I felt like I was really getting into a groove and 64-66 felt smooth and fun.

We went out a tiny bit slow and I was sitting in 3rd for the first two laps or so. I definitely just fell asleep somewhere but I’m not sure where. My body had so much lactic acid that I didn’t feel like I could kick but then I found another gear with like 50m to go which meant I could’ve gone before that. I think I was actually racing the last 50m, now I just have to do that for the entire thing. Finally got the mindset back, it just took a few 1500s

Activity Name: Thoughts on the new Strava font?
Description: 4x100m strides. The strides felt okay but definitely not the best. Race tomorrow at like 7pm, another 1500. Ran with Alize today so it wasn’t as quick and I’m hoping my body will thank me tomorrow.
Was going to go further but we have a house tour at noon and time got ahead of me. I felt decent honestly and just decided to stay really local and do some loops.

VERY wet and VERY cold today but honestly I still enjoyed myself. There were a lot of worms and I avoided every one that I saw 🤷‍♂️. Honestly I’m surprised I ran slightly faster than normal, I think my body is feeling pretty good!

It was very windy surprisingly but other than that it was beautiful. I felt very slow and just let my body do what it wanted. My body felt like it hated me for this mornings session so I didn’t push anything.

2:47.4, 2:48.7, 2:48.3, 2:48.8, 2:45.7. I think I was a little scared of this workout before hand but it honestly ended up being not too bad. I think right now I’m in about 14:00 shape on a perfect day so there is still work to be done but I feel great about where I’m at. The reps wouldn’t really get hard until 600-800 in and from there it still wasn’t as bad as trying to run 60s 400s… it was a beautiful morning today! I just wish I had some company, I think I could’ve gone even quicker :).

Activity Name: I was today years old when I learned that garmins stop showing tenths of seconds after 15 minutes

Description: 4x100m strides. The weather was awesome for the double. The strides felt pretty solid. Fast workout tomorrow so hopefully it’ll feel good.

Activity Name: Excited to join Bowerman Track Club!
Description: It’s been a long time coming but I finally found a team that aligns with my needs as an athlete! Today felt really good, it was an absolutely beautiful morning and Eugene has been popping off the last few days.
Headed out to Iris Ridge for the double. It was definitely a lot of gain but it was fun and absolutely beautiful! Just like Alize Hartke
EZ 6 to go see blanket man with Alize Hartke. Some good chats today and honestly it flew by! My body will thank me tomorrow for running with Alize.

Ran out to a neighborhood that I haven’t been to for a while which was nice. I’m actually surprised that I averaged sub 7 but I feel like on the longer runs I get pretty warmed up and feeling good the last few miles.
Went up to the reservoir to get a little bit of dirt. I didn’t feel horrible but my body did feel like it was coming out of hibernation… that’s okay though, it just means take it slower!

3:43, 3:42, 3:44, 3:42, 3:41, 3:40, 3:41, 3:40; 21.9, 20.8, 20.9, 20.6. This workout was perfect for today. I am still a little sore from the 5k but it was just the right pace to challenge me a little bit without digging deeper. The 150s were okay but I have a little groin pain that makes top end feel dangerous so I held back a little. The 1200s I’d always come through the first lap quick and then settle in. Really happy with this one!
Middle 9 miles w/ unique hartke
Went to fleet feet to get a few gels. One for tomorrow and one for a tester. I actually felt really good today and enjoyed myself out there!

5:11, 5:09, 5:03, 5:00, 4:56, 4:51, 4:46, 4:39. Was aiming to start at 5:12 and work down 4 seconds each mile and then the last was supposed to be 4:42. I got out later than expected so it was a little warm and at times a little windy but not too bad on either front. The first four I did backwards and then the last four were normal. I doubted myself a few times during this but the last mile actually ended up feeling pretty reasonable and not too bad.
Did a 7 mile loop with Seth Totten and honestly it flew by! Lots of stuff to catch up on and totally worth waking up a little earlier than normal.

Activity Name: 5 solo + 6 w/ Unique + 1 solo = 12 EZ miles

Description: Pretty chill evening run and nice weather. Had to do a tiny bit of dog-dging and there were some bugs here and there but everything else was good.

10:32, 10:24, 10:29, 10:23. I didn’t fully lock in today so my splits weren’t super consistent but they weren’t too bad either. I felt really good this morning going reverse. Couldn’t have asked for a better morning!

Lots of puddles (aka creeks) and stuff to cross so there were slowdowns here and there but it wasn’t too bad. Overall a solid LR. The goal was to progress throughout the run which was very natural, I had to CD the last 2 miles because I was getting a little spicy and needed to recover quickly after this.

We had a very slow first lap but followed it up with three  laps which I’m pretty happy with. I think even though I wasn’t feeling super good today I definitely could’ve PRed with a quicker opening lap which is a good sign!
I ran 4, then around 5 with Zay and Brady and then the rest solo.
I ran Mestler’s warmup and then jogged around til 5. Somehow I got roped into a tempo 800 🤷‍♂️

Activity Name: 4x(800, 400, 200 w/ 90” rest) w/ 3:00 jog | WAP goes crazy on this one
Description: 2:19.4, 63.9, 30.1; 2:15.2, 64.9, 30.2; 2:14.8, 64.7, 30.1; 2:14.7, 64.7, 29.9. It was windy as heck today, gusts of 20+ mph and a pretty constant headwind on the home stretch. I was aiming for 2:16, 65, 30 so I was still right on pace but it was a struggle on some of the reps. Before the workout I felt like I had no energy but by the last few sets I felt pretty solid. It wasn’t a perfect day but not the worst either. 1500 coming up on Friday so this effort was a little shorter.
W/ Alize Hartke

What a day! The weather was perfect, pacing was solid, and I felt pretty good too. The first 7 laps were paced and I was feeling a little antsy so the pacer stepped off and the last 5.5 laps I lead. The last 1600 was 4:20.39, the last 3200 was 8:46.80 (8:12.80 last 3k). I’m really happy with closing in 64.89, 62.35 so 2:07.24 even when I felt as lactic as I did. Also averaging 66.20 is something I never thought I’d be able to do but here we are! Seems like cracking into the 65s is the next step!

First time running with Alex Ostberg, thanks Alex Merder for the contact info, sorry Alex  Helmuth  for running with someone besides you but once you start again we’ll link up. Also ran into Eli Rosen-Duran which was an amazing surprise. 4 strides afterwards in spikes felt pretty solid, definitely feeling kind of fresh and ready to rip.
Ran with Zay and Brady, both whom were struggling with their allergies pretty aggressively. Hopefully Zyrtec will be the answer 🫡

I’ve been training in vomeros since around October I think and I really enjoy them but these days I look forward to running in the dream chasers (rabbit shoe) way more. They might even become my new daily trainer soon :0

Activity Name: Been a while since the last rendition of “doing Zay’s workout”
Description: Down week this week so the medium long is shorter than normal 😍. Alize had 3xmile (she told me 2xmile before the workout) and 6x200 so I thought I might as well do it with her. It really makes the run fly by!

Activity Name: First weights session in a while
Description:
I race this weekend and haven’t done weights for quite some time so I ended up going very light. 

Warmup (10 reps each)
Glute Bridge
Single Leg Glute Bridge
RDL
Single Leg RDL
Single Leg Balance (30 seconds each leg)
Squat

Main (2 sets x 10 reps)
KB Squat - first set no weight then 30lb
KB Row - 30lb
KB Backwards Lunge - 30lb

Kinda feeling the rabbit shoes today, they felt good even on the strides! No rain in the forecast but it rained the whole time except for the last half mile which was blue skies with a rainbow…? Eugene weather never ceases to surprise me.
We rallied a lot but also played 3 games and I ended up losing 2 😢

I had no expectations for the LR this morning but my body kept wanting to grind and I forced myself to slow down a few times. Overall had a great morning and didn’t force anything at all! I got attacked by the bird at Alton baker but it didn’t really affect me at all. Lol Strava actually thinks my average heart rate was above 180 for this whole thing…

Inspired by Gilbert Grundy. This was Alex  Helmuth  and I’s first time out here so we were wandering around for 2 miles before we found the actual route which was kind of fun but also kind of annoying. It ended up being worth it though!
Feeling very slow after the workout this morning but at least the weather was nice!

67.6, 65.4, 65.3, 64.3, 66.0, 64.4, 63.6, 65.0, 65.5, 65.8; 29.8, 29.8, 29.3, 30.8, 29.6, 30.4, 29.3, 29.2. Was shooting for 65 and 29-30 so after the first rep it was pretty spot on. It was a little windy out there and it is pretty easy to tell which of the 200s were windy…
4x100m track strides.
Alize Hartke and I ran on the treadmill today. It was a little boring to start but honestly not too bad by the end.

4:46.8, 20:35.7 (5:09/1600), 4:49.1. Ran with Moi Martinez today which gave me way more motivation to actually get out of bed and workout. The entire workout felt really smooth and comfortable. My body definitely wanted to go a bit quicker. I think after Saturday was so difficult and fast my body was confused as to why I was going so slow…
The four strides felt okay. I’m definitely feeling some fatigue after that 5k, I don’t know if I’ve ever raced that hard in my entire life.
I ran to the reservoir in the dream chasers today and felt surprisingly good!

Connor Frisch |  made it 6 miles and AleAlex  Helmuthdid his 12 miles with me and then I did 4 solo. The first 12 was very smooth and comfortable and felt REALLY good so mile 13 I started to push a little and my body felt really good but I was breathing a little harder than normal maybe. Overall an awesome day at Dorena!

Activity Name: Pre Classic Night of Miles Community Event
Description: Honestly I was prepping for this as if I were trying to run quick and everything was going great. Then I had a few things that slowed me down before warmup and put my head in the wrong place. Didn’t give myself enough time on the warmup and then ended up being delayed by ~22 minutes. Finally the gun went off and there were supposed to be pace lights for 4:00 that I could use as reference but they were absolutely running away from me which discouraged me a ton. They ended up being WR pace… and I had absolutely no competition or people cheering really. It was just like a solo Covid time trial but with less knowledge of where I was at and I just went into workout mode after the opening lap. Not proud of today, but I can’t say I really raced… I still think every 1500 or mile I do is a step in the right direction and I did have a pretty tough workout Tuesday and lifting Tuesday that I was definitely not fully recovered from.
The spikes strides felt okay
Trying to go a little later since I race late tomorrow night.

Activity Name: Saw a lot of interesting things today
Description: Rain+sun+wind, spider mama, beaver, baby snek, feet, buttcrack, and more.

Warmup (10 reps each)
Glute Bridge
Single Leg Glute Bridge
RDL
Single Leg RDL
Single Leg Balance (30 seconds each leg)
Squat

Main (2 sets x 10 reps)
BB Squat - 60lb
BB Row - 60lb
BB Backwards Lunge - 60lb

2x10 pushups
2x10 fire hydrants
1’ crunches -> 1’ pretzel crunches -> 1’ bicycles
Accidentally wore my older vomeros but I didn’t even notice until after.

2:49.2, 2:50.4, 2:48.6, 2:48.1, 2:49.5, 2:50.1, 2:49.1, 2:49.6, 2:49.5, 2:48.6. 67s-68s are feeling good in terms of form but I just had zero energy today from the moment I woke up. I was breathing pretty hard by the end of these reps and had some lactate floating around but they still felt pretty good and weren’t super mentally tough. Would’ve loved some company out there but actually didn’t need it to have a great workout! If you string together all the 1ks it would be 28:12.7.
Just kind of ran around today. Alize and I are looking at moving soon so maybe we won’t have to worry about soft surfaces anymore! Strides and double this evening.
Just basically did two 6 mile loops and then added 2 afterwards. I felt good today, it was all about recovery and I never pushed anything.

67.7, 68.9, 66.8, 67.2, 66.9, 67.8, 67.8, 67.0, 67.1, 68.0, 67.0, 66.6, 67.9, 67.7, 68.9, 67.1, 66.4, 66.9, 67.2, 66.6, 68.1, 67.9, 67.6, 68.4, 65.9. 28:05.4 if you sum all 10k of the 400s together. The first 13 were forward and the last 12 were reverse. These felt really good, especially the ones where Moi Martinez biked with me! If this workout didn’t feel good I would’ve been in trouble. I don’t think I can run 28:05 but I think I can run a few seconds slower than that.
The first few strides felt okay but the last two felt really good

Activity Name: 10x600 w/ 1’ rest, bathroom break+300 jog, 5x300 w/ 1’ jog
Description: 1:41.2, 1:42.4, 1:42.3, 1:40.7, 1:41.8, 1:41.3, 1:40.8, 1:40.9, 1:40.7, 1:41.4; 48.3, 46.3, 46.2, 46.1, 44.7. The goal was 1: and 46-48 so I was right on pace for most reps. Today felt really good physically! I think I was lacking a little bit of motivation but other than that every rep felt strong and pretty comfortable. My form and breathing was much more controlled than when I did 300s some 2 months ago at the same pace with more rest. This was a good confidence booster today and something that I think my body will recover well from.
Meanwhile me going 7:00 pace: 🤨
4 strides.
Ran with Hayden Cox, Alize Hartke, Allen, and Peri. I felt better than I expected but definitely feeling some soreness and such.

I am kind of speechless. I knew I was fit enough to run ~28:30 and was planning on going out at 14:10 pace. Pacers were supposed to go 13:55-14:00 but I think they ended up going through at 14:08 which was perfect, I came through in 14:11. Before the race I was struggling to visualize a way that this race went well since the pacers were supposed to go too fast and I thought I’d be leading a secondary pack. Instead of that I ended up being on the back of the front pack the entire way and made moves whenever people started to fall off. I was struggling mentally the entire race and had to make so many moves but somehow my body just kept going even when I felt like I had nothing left!

5:11, 5:09, 5:09, 5:09; 33.4, 33.8, 34.4, 34.5, 33.8, 34.2, 34.0, 34.2. Super easy workout today! Was shooting for 5:12-5:16 and 33-35 so every rep was perfect. I have 3 days to recover after this before the PTF 10k so I’m hoping to feel absolutely stellar on Saturday.
This lollipop was exactly 6 miles which was awesome. Felt okay today, not good but not bad. I think 14 miles of bark might honestly be too much, since things felt a little weird.

Activity Name: Easy double | when I really don’t feel like doubling is when I feel the worst

Description: Warmed up to a half mile bark loop and did some 5’ reps with 2.5’ jog. Avg according to watch: 5:15, 5:15, 5:11, 5:12, 5:00. There are signs saying it’s a half mile loop which makes more sense than my watch. For one rep I came through the loop in 2:25 and my watch said 5:16 average and then I came through 2 loops in 4:50 and my watch said 5:12 average. Definitely wonky but either way it was an effort based workout and felt really good! The last one I did reverse because my body was starting to feel out of line.

Chatted to William Fallini-Haas, Anthony Benitez, and John Bennett while making loops around the reservoir and avoiding the big ass lawn mower… I felt great today, definitely shaking off the soreness from Saturday and feeling good again.

The faster I went today the better I felt. 6:15 didn’t necessarily feel good to start but I just kept increasing the pace and eventually ended in a 5:12 in trainers on sidewalks and roads so I’m pretty happy with how that went today. The goal was to not need a cooldown so I think I did well out there.

I’m still trying to wrap my head around Saturdays race. It was so quick and I feel like I just leveled up 30 times. It makes me feel all kinds of ways, mostly surprised and a little giddy thinking about how fast that is. I’m also significantly the most sore I’ve been since the marathon trials so that tells me that I went very hard and probably couldn’t have given any more if any at all. Doesn’t look like I’ll make the trials, I’m sitting at 28th and 24 go.
Drove back to Eugene this morning, worked the day and then got out for a nice and warm easy 4. Felt pretty solid but definitely sore.
Gotta drive back to Eugene today and double and work a full day so obviously had to wake up a little earlier. Honestly it was really peaceful out there but a little boring.
Picked up Harlan and then ran to Runhub and did the community run and then added another loop and came back home. Ended up being pretty perfect!

Tried to get a feel for mile race pace by doing 409 meters of strides. The first two felt okay but the last two actually felt pretty solid. I have another community mile tomorrow so we’ll see how that goes.
Had a great time with the brooks peeps! Tried out the Hyperion Max 2s and got a ton of goodies afterwards :). I’ll definitely be back another day this week.

Medium long got pushed back to Thursday this week. Just went all the way up high and then the AB loop with a little past the 5. I’ve been enjoying running from home which is something I didn’t think I’d say for a while…
I love being able to run soft surface whenever I want!
0.3 miles to Amazon + 3 mile loops + 2 1k loops + 0.3 miles back home ended up working out pretty well. I didn’t actually get bored or anything.

5:05.5, 5:06.8, 5:03.7, 5:05.3, 5:05.1; 35.3, 33.7, 33.5, 32.8, 32.4, 32.0, 33.1, 33.0. Warmed up with Moi Martinez and Alex  Helmuth and then Alex jumped in on 3 of the mile reps and 4 of the 200s which was nice. The miles felt really easy and the 200s weren’t difficult but they didn’t really feel like 5k pace. I was trying to get 32.5-33 to feel comfortable but I think I’m still recovering from the 10k 10 days ago.
4x100m strides worked into the end. Ran into Mestler after a boring first few miles so that was nice. The South Eugene turf felt like it was taking all my energy today.

Activity Name: Running from home is the best now
Description: We are 0.30 miles from Amazon and south Eugene now which is awesome! I knew it would be good being closer to central Eugene but I think I underestimated how great it would be. Location, location, location.
Ran with Moi and Alex and we had a good time out there!

Activity Name: Didn’t start my watch til a mile in :(

Description: Saw a coyote on my little solo 3 miles. This community run flew by, the people at Tracksmith are great!

Activity Name: Finally stumbled upon the brooks segment
Description: Ran to Runhub and ran with Moi for a little over 7 miles and then back home. My body definitely feels a little zapped from yesterday but not too bad at the same time. We didn’t really end up doing any of the community run things but oh well!
Getting between 4 and 6 miles is so easy from our new place and it’s like all soft surface haha. Couldn’t ask for much more.

Activity Name: 800 all out, 10’ rest, 4x300 w/ 3’ rest, 4x150 w/ walk back rest
Description: 57->62.9=1:59.9 for the 800; 45.8, 44.8, 44.5, 44 (adjusted for late split); 21.7, 21.7, 21.1, 21.1. Doing a solo 800 that way was insanely difficult and impossible to recover from. I was tying up the last 300+ meters and I’m honestly surprised I was still able to run a 62. I feel like I have a stamina meter like in a video game but then when I use all of that stamina it doesn’t go back to what it was before, even after full recovery. I was ready to rip some 300s but after the 800 my body didn’t have enough stamina to do anything crazy. In other instances I feel like I can only use my top gear like once a month and when I do it goes away for a while. My body is just not built to clear lactate as efficiently as an 800/1500 guy and I recognize that but it’s still frustrating at times.

Activity Name: Easy Double + Nike Event | Worst running event I’ve ever been to
Double dip | Citius Mag/NB Run -> Leading Tinman Run
Description: The Citius Mag/NB run was around 4 miles and the fastest last 800m down agate won a hat, so I ran 2:17 even with obstacles and stuff so that was fun. Then I led the Tinman run after some confusion at Amazon… wasn’t supposed to go this far but I didn’t want people getting lost haha
Had to take some walk breaks the last mile iykyk
I really enjoyed this community run, probably my favorite so far. Tracksmith has a really genuine group and they’re fun to run with!

My watch missed about a quarter mile according to Mestler's coros. Ended up buying a new watch afterwards so I'll be able to run places with trees and not worry about missing out on mileage. We did a little bit of a progression but I stuck to my easy run limits today. It was a little warm but pretty shaded so it was nice.
Easy 6 before making the 7 hour drive back to Eugene.

Activity Name: I think we hit 109-110 during this one
Description: I felt better today than the hot doubles earlier in the week. Maybe I’m getting used to it?

30.4, 31.4, 2:11.2; 30.6, 29.9, 2:11.7; 31.8, 30.3, 2:09.8; 30.8, 31.0, 2:11; 30.9, 30.7, 2:10.2. I was shooting for 30-31 and 2:10-2:12 so I was pretty much right on pace for everything. The first set was pretty difficult but from there it was a good kind of difficult. I wasn't building much lactate which was good but it was pretty darn hot out there. It got to 80+ degrees by the end of it. Connor Frisch |  helped me out with some of the reps in there. Took some sips of water between sets to try and stay hydrated.

Activity Name:
One-hundred and eight
I got cooked on the asphalt
Did not feel that great
Running the Folsom firecracker 5k w/ Unique and Connor
Description: That course is definitely not something that I’d want to do so I’m glad I wasn’t racing… I felt solid today on the run and it wasn’t super hot out yet.

Woke up at 6 to try and get my run done before it gets to 110°… Honestly it was somewhat nice out there. My body hated waking up after less than 6 hours of sleep but after a mile or so it felt pretty good. Miscalculated mileage somehow while I was running and the goats are blocking part of the trail bit I still enjoyed it.

Activity Name: The weather cooled off for me, it was only 104° by the time I finished up
Description: It was hot but honestly not bad in the shade.

4:58.0, 4:58.7, 4:58.2, 4:58.8, 4:57.9, 4:58.1. The first three were normal direction and felt really comfortable, I had to slow myself down a little bit. The last three were reverse and felt good but I did have to focus up a little bit to keep myself on pace. I felt pretty recovered today despite racing and working out only 2 days ago. We’re driving to Sacramento today so I wanted to get a workout in before heading into the heat. Threshold is feeling really good although it kind of always has and it should with longer rest. The goal today was 4:56-5:00 so all of them were right on. Sometimes I’d go out in like a 73 but nothing faster.
Just went out 2 miles, flipped, and did some strides at south Eugene. The strides felt pretty solid, I got the pace down to mildly quick at the end.
Picked up Moi on my way to Dorris for an early morning run!
Location: Dorris Ranch Living History Farm, USA

Description: My watch actually works out here now!!! Upgraded from 235 to 255, so far it has been a wonderful journey.

They said I’ll still get charged on the 17th for another month even though I’m canceling on the 12th… kinda BS but whatever… I felt really good on the tready today. I was watching YouTube the whole time and it honestly felt like I wasn’t even running.

Activity Name: CD w/ my favorite person ever

Description: 10:01.8, 47.5, 48.2, 48.6, 47.2, 48.1, 46.6, 48.2, 47.4, 47.4, 48.2. I was aiming for 5:00-5:05 for the full 2 mile rep and 47.5-48.5 on the 300s. Surprisingly I didn’t hit a single rep between 47.6 and 48.1 which kind of goes to show that I wasn’t perfectly locked in for the 300s. I felt really good today though, I felt like I was holding back throughout the whole workout and could’ve gone another 400 at sub 60 after each rep. The 300s nearly felt like 5k pace which is scary but also was a huge confidence boost!

I finally felt a little revived this evening. I ran in the rabbit shoes after not running in them in a while; I had forgotten how soft they are. The strides felt really good too although the track was pretty windy. Also this was my first run with my new forerunner 255!!! Also ran into Mestler and Karen so that was great too!

I ran with Jack Mntherly today, we did a 2 mile loop with Moi Martinez and then a 5 mile loop out Amazon. I went literally the exact same pace as yesterday but it’s just what felt good to my body 🤷‍♂️. My legs felt a little beat up today and yesterday but I think I’ll feel really recovered by next week.
Ran with Zay for around 4 miles and then did an Amazon loop. I have been loving this route! I think my body needed this type of recovery run although it is more TOF (time on feet).

44.0, 30.0, 13.8; 43.9, 29.8, 14.0; 43.0, 28.4, 14.0; 42.6, 27.6, 13.8; 41.5, 27.4, 13.3. First three sets were in vaporflys and the last two in my old dragonflys. I did the whole workout with Mestler which was perfect! I surprised myself a lot during this workout since I didn’t think I’d be going faster than 43s or 28s today. It was only 3k of work, but that’s most definitely my fastest 3k of work ever. The rest was the perfect amount and I never felt like I was way over my head. This workout did kind of make me realize that if I really want to be in contention to make a world team then I need to be able to run this fast at the end of a fast race…
Started out EXTREMELY slow today but I just kept chugging and my body warmed up eventually. DMV appointment right after this and double this evening.

Activity Name: Easy Eight w/ Xian and Zay
Description: Getting dropped by Xian Shively and Alize Hartke. Feeling sore from yesterday.

What an awesome race! It started out very hot and I wasn’t sure I’d be able to keep it but I tried to keep it going and anytime I felt like the pace was settling I would move up. Before I knew it I was in third and making ground on the two leaders. I took the lead with a lap to go and injected some pace but ended up running 61 last lap as opposed to the winner 57 and 2nd 59.

Activity Name: WU | Tried to keep it flat
Shakeout for Sound Running Sunset Tour 5k

Description: 4x100m spikes strides. Felt good today but it’s really hard to find 5k pace. I would either try to be relaxed and go too slow or try to push it a bit and go too fast.
I don’t know if I fully trust my HRM on the watch but it was very low most of the time… Just another slight confidence boost going into Saturday.

Activity Name: Accidentally went 9 when I was supposed to go 8...
Description: Good thing my coach isn't awake yet. Ran with Alex  Helmuth and ran into Mestler on Amazon. I felt pretty good today and the weather was perfect.
Ran to Runhub to try on and check out some shoes. Met Alex and Zay there.

5:08.3, 5:12.2, 5:11.9; 32.7, 32.2, 32.5, 31.8, 32.2, 31.6. I felt really good today. Was shooting for 5:12 and 32-33 and hit pace on mostly everything. The first 1600 I swear I was on pace through 1200 but I must've gotten a little antsy. The miles were easy physically but hard to get just right. I was trying to focus on going 5k effort on the 200s and honestly I think that I can run a pretty fast 5k... It's going to feel like a sprint but I think my body can handle it.

The highlight of the run was having a CRISPY high 5 with Mestler. I felt really good, I definitely am fully recovered from all workouts and runs and feeling better and better every day. Ready to roll on Saturday! Sound running sunset tour 5k should be a good one.
Alize Hartke

Activity Name: Trying out the new bike trail
Description: I had run parts of this trail before but they connected a whole bunch of stuff and added a ton of new bike trail recently. I’m definitely going to have to find the end at some point.

I was trying to go 5 and ended up going nearly a half mile over. Oopsie. I think since I’ve been watching the Olympics I’ve been wanting to run fast (mentally) but physically I’m not quite there yet. Tomorrow will be 8 miles so we’ll see how I’m feeling.

I accidentally ran the wrong way (I was planning on a different route) but ended up just rolling with it. I felt good today but I think it’s going to take a long time for my breathing to catch up to my legs.
I’m a little sore from weights yesterday but I still felt good! I’m actually already looking forward to working out!

Activity Name: First lifting session of the season
Description:
Normal warmup
2x10:
Bar squat (10lb each side)
DB row (35lb)
Reverse lunge (no weight)
3’ of core after
I would’ve gone heavier on the squat and reverse lunge but my inner right thigh felt like it was going to cramp up or break or something, idk.

Activity Name: New watch -> all my mile markers are wrong
Description: I felt surprisingly good today. Day 2 of running after a 2 week break. I tried the gel nimbus 26 for the first time and really enjoyed them, I might be getting a few more pairs soon!

I took a FULL 2 weeks off and today was my first day back! It started off a little rough and I’m definitely out of shape (relative to 2 weeks ago), but eventually it actually felt good to run again. I’m really excited for this season, I just have to work everything out in terms of flights, vacations, races, etc. I drove to Sac yesterday and will be here for about a week so I had to do my trustee 4 mile loop to kick things off.
W/ Michael Chambers & Connor Frisch |
Classic 7am fish hatch w/ Connor Frisch |  and Mahkai Davis-MacíasMahkai Davis-Macías.

I’m definitely still not fit (it’s week 2) but running has been really enjoyable! Last night and slightly into this morning I was finishing up some work so I didn’t get a ton of sleep but I’m hoping to get more sleep tomorrow and take Friday off of work.
I was a little sore before the run from weights and the bike ride yesterday (back and butt) but once we got running I didn’t feel it at all. The run flew by and I’m starting to feel ready to workout!

Warmup

Main set
3x10 leg weight pushes 205 lb
3x10 calf raise 175 lb
3x10 lat pull down 100 -> 110 -> 120 lb

Cooldown
2x15 fire hydrants
2x10 donkey kicks
3’ core

This bike was pretty fun! I did a 10 minute warmup, followed by 30 minutes of 0.25 on 0.25 off, then 5 minute cooldown. The ons I averaged around 260-274 watts allegedly and the offs I averaged 163-173 watts allegedly. My heart rate got up to as high as like 160-170 but usually was between 140 and 150.

Activity Name: Easy 6 + 4 x 100m all out w/ full recovery
Description: The 4 all out strides were decent. None of them were super fast but mechanically I felt okay.
Sprinkled 7x30”on/30” off about 7 miles in. I’d say this was m my first “long run” of the season! It definitely felt good

w/ Alize Hartke & Brady Lance. Ran the Willamette Confluence Preserve (maybe WCP from now on) with the homies. It was nice out there despite the absolute DOWNPOUR yesterday. I think I’ll be coming out here again tomorrow so it was a good scouting run!
w/ Alex  Helmuth. None of my friends like bark

W/ Alex  Helmuth & Alize Hartke 
WU
Normal warmup

3x10
Squats (Bar -> 10 on each -> 10 on each)
Forward lunges (25 lb plate)
Bench press (5 on each -> 10 on each -> 10 on each)

2x5 pull ups
2x15 donkey kick

CD (w/ 12 lb med ball)
1’ Russian twist
1’ sit ups
1’ suitcases

10’ WU, 8x2’on/1’off, 10’ CD. The resistance went up to 25 and I did the warmup and cooldown at ~15, the offs at 12, and the ons at 18. I was definitely breathing a bit on the ons. The whole workout flew by! This was my first time trying the shokz and spinning at the YMCA.

Activity Name: Zay WU + Workout + CD W/ Moi

Description: W/ Alex  Helmuth and Alize Hartke. We did an Amazon loop and then headed up through downtown and back. My last 3 miles were supposed to be between 5:45 and 6:00 which wasn’t easy because of the lights and miscellaneous downtown things but it ended up working out!
It’s good to be back home!

Activity Name: Narada Falls -> Reflection Lakes -> Narada falls trail

Description: Paces for the 5’ reps were allegedly: 5:08, 5:07, 5:07, 5:05. The 2’ recovery honestly felt like I wasn’t fully recovered after for whatever reason but the ons felt pretty good. It definitely wasn’t “easy”, but I think it was the right effort. Years ago I would’ve been disappointed with this workout but now I realize it’s a good sign for a good season (I used to rip early season workouts)
The map made no sense so we kinda just walked wherever. Fun little walk!

Activity Name: No sleep + stomach feeling weird, but the views made up for it
Description: Was planning on 10 but ended up doing 9 instead.
The waterfall hike was easy and then we decided to do the storm king hike which ended up being very technical and straight uphill for what felt like miles. I’d say the views were worth it though!!!

The minutes average paces were: 5:11, 5:08, 5:06, 5:11, 5:14, 5:06, 5:17, 5:11, 5:06, 5:14. The first 6 ish miles was with Alize Hartke and some special guest miles with Brady Lance. Then I started my 10x1’on/1’off @ LT. The pickups felt awesome, even in my gel nimbus 26s… I think they actually thrive going a little quicker but the uphills were slightly tougher than normal. Great long run and workout out there! Perfect weather. It’s kind of difficult to lock in a pace at Dorris, I kept switching between T and a little slower than LT but I think the effort was perfect.
Location: Dorris Ranch Living History Farm, USA

Description: This was kind of more like a time trial thingy between Alex  Helmuth and I which was super fun! The course ran through mostly the bark at Lane CC and had some sharp turns, uneven bark/grass, 1 steep uphill and downhill (repeated once each), and a few hay bales. I think I was a little overzealous the first half mile and mile but once we settled in it felt really good. This is week 6 so given the course that was about what I was expecting for today. We went out there to have fun and get some good work in and that’s exactly what we did so I think today was perfect! Thanks coach Alize Hartke and Lonn Robertson for rooting us on!
4x100m strides. w/ Alize Hartke & Brady Lance.

Alize Hartke had 6x1k @3:40-3:45 so I joined in and it ended up working out well. It’s always more fun to do her workouts than just an easy run. I ran in the border between lane 1 and 2 the whole time

10:30, 10:24, 10:24. First run in the new vapes. Ran with Alex  Helmuth for the whole workout which was awesome! We basically perfect split the whole thing. I felt really good today physically but both Alize and I had upset stomachs this morning for whatever reason.
W/ Alex  Helmuth and Ku Stevens

The goal of winning a free Alaskan round trip flight anywhere they fly was obtained! Originally the plan was to just go with the leader(s) and then go with like a mile to go. The first 4 miles we went out in like 5:10 pace and the leader started to drop off so I just kept up the pace and slowly made a gap. The whole race was supposed to be a “sidewalk race” and there was at least one turn that wasn’t really marked at all so I’m glad I brought my phone with me with the course map. I ended up almost never on the sidewalk since it would’ve been harder and more dangerous. I definitely went a little harder than prescribed and my body actually felt it a bit afterwards but still the effort wasn’t anywhere near race pace. I don’t recover very well after using the endorphin speeds (3s) so I don’t think I’ll wear them for anything besides long runs when needed.
W/ Ku Stevens and Alex  Helmuth
Nice easy Amazon loop with Josh and Jenny. Today is day 3 of doing PT exercises and I felt really good starting the run and I don’t think I had any pain the entire time.
We ended up just running Amazon and then doing a campus loop kind of and a few track laps. I felt good today, this was day 2 of doing my PT stretches that Alize found and they’ve been working well.
Listened to music and ran through some random trails, not sure if I liked the trail video thing but the music got me going!

5:15.4, 5:12.7, 5:10.5, 5:11.0, 5:12.2, 5:13. W/ Alex  Helmuth. I think today I finally got used to running with other people in a workout again. Mentally I just always think too much but I just trusted Alex on the last two reps that he led and trusted myself on the last 2 reps I led which made things go by quicker and easier. The effort was extremely low which was great! I’ve come to love threshold days since I’m not racing every workout like I used to. Everything just felt right today and I’m already looking forward to the next threshold day with Alex!

4x100m track strides. I listened to music on the run today which made me realize that I’m not used to that yet. I’ve been running without music for so long that my mind wanders much more when running without music (which makes the run go by faster). The strides were much better with music though and they were more fun than usual. Overall a great start to the week.

Ran 6.75 or so solo and did the rest with Connor Frisch |  I felt pretty good to start and started moving a little bit but by the end I was feeling a little beat up. I didn’t eat anything before so maybe that was it, not sure. Next Sunday is going to HURT!
W/ Jef Ritter. It is warm in Sac haha

10:05.8 (5:03 mid, 5:02 mid); 49.57, 52.70, 52.33, 52.30, 51.15, 51.57, 51.12, 51.42, 51.26, 51.32; 32.54, 32.64, 32.91, 32.20, 32.70, 33.07, 31.95, 31.34. I started out a little hot for the threshold but got a good rhythm after that. My breathing was harder than expected but everything else felt easier than expected. The 300s went really well, it almost felt like I could run my 10k pace for a 10k 😳. The 200s were pretty easy and it felt good to get going a little bit. I think 32s feel insanely different than what they used to like 1-2 years ago. Overall an awesome workout and thanks to tm8 @Alex  Helmuth and cwoach @AlizeHartke for coming out to support me!
4 x 100m track strides afterwards.
W/ (in no particular order) Alex  Helmuth, Moi Martinez, Josh Park, Nick, and Mesty

5:07.5; 5:14, 5:16, 5:15, 5:14 = 20:59; 5:03.8. Very easy workout today but I feel like it’s building me up. I was pretty consistent for every rep and felt very comfortable and smooth during the reps. I definitely wanted to rip sub 5 the last mile but even 5:04 felt like I was holding back. I’m glad I took the extra day to recover, I think it was a good idea for my body.

Today was Moi Martinez’s first day on railroad 🤩. Now we’ve got a solid group of 3 to lift, workout, and run with (and hang out). We ended up doing Alex’s warmup since I’m too sore to workout today and Moi is just getting going. The run really flew by!
It felt like this took forever haha.

Activity Name: Yes, I’m feeling it now Mr. Krabs
Description: I’m a little sore from yesterday which isn’t too surprising. I think during the run it felt really good but a 9 mile tempo at 5:08 on that course or anywhere really is no joke for my 4th week of workouts. If I knew I’d have to run a tempo as opposed to just a quicker long run I would’ve worn vaporflys. The endorphin speed is just not built for that, at least for me. The run today felt good, I tried to focus on letting the body take the reins.

Activity Name: Rock n Roll Half Marathon Workout
Description: Got through 4 miles on pace but Alex just wasn’t feeling like today was the day so we decided to slow it down so we didn’t dig ourselves too deep of a hole. We both got a good workout in and right now that’s all we need!
w/ Seth Totten. It was really relaxing today out there for some reason, my legs felt like they weren't even running. That is definitely a good sign for Sunday's half marathon at San Jose rock n roll.

Activity Name: EZ 9 w/ Connor and Walker @GB Practice
Description: W/ Connor Frisch | the.running.statisticianWalker KnaussConnor Frisch |  up meeting at the GB practice and ran to Miner’s ravine which was a blast from the past. I felt pretty solid today, much better than last night. It was nice seeing Carla Rose and Jeffrey Adkins too!
It was 102° for the double so I stayed in the shade and it wasn’t too bad. I definitely felt sluggish for some reason but I have 3 days to fully recover coming up which is good!

5:14.4, 5:10, 5:06, 5:09, 5:09; 33.4, 31.9, 31.8, 33.2, 31.9, 31.7, 32.5, 31.2. Seth Totten and I did the first 1600 on the track and we were planning on alternating with a mile loop every other rep but then they sprayed the infield of the track with insecticides or something during rep 2 so we stayed on the mile loop. The mile loop was pretty awesome and we were a little quick on most of them but they felt good!
2 mile warmup, 4x5’ on/2’ off, cooldown to 7.
I felt a little sluggish this morning after staying up kind of late last night but it wasn’t too bad.

Activity Name: Easy 6 w/ Zay | 80.00 miles this week completely on accident
Description: Alize Hartke did some solo miles and then I joined for the last 6 miles of her run.

Activity Name: 4 mile WU, 8 mile @steady state, 4 mile CD
Description: The 8 mile steady state in the middle was around 5:46 pace. Definitely a great day to bring out the Hyperion max 2s, they felt great for this type of pace/effort. Did the whole thing with Alex  Helmuth. Moi Martinez joined us for the first 4 miles which was nice!

4x100m track strides. Tried a new-ish route today with Alex  Helmuth for the double. Overall I felt okay and I’m definitely ready for a workout tomorrow! Definitely not the best strides I’ve ever had but not bad.

Ran 6 easy w/ Moi Martinez and then did another 2 to finish up. The run went by so quick since we took a different route and I had great company 🥰. The fresh foam x v4 are awesome, they feel so normal when walking around but while running they just feel super protective. Definitely can feel that there’s no plate or anything of the sort though.
w/ Gilbert Grundy for the first 6 or so. I felt pretty decent today, definitely better than the double yesterday.
I thought I’d feel a lot better this evening after the workout but I’ve definitely had better post workout doubles before.

3:15, 3:11, 3:15, 3:10, 3:14, 3:14, 3:16, 3:15, 3:14, 3:09. The reps definitely weren’t accurate but I think maybe the last 5 were really close. My watch said our slowest rep was 5:14 and our fastest was 5:04 so I think the effort was perfect today. These were on a dirt track and I feel like my legs were recovered immediately after the workout. Alex  Helmuth and I alternated reps so this one flew by!!

4x100m track strides. Did the run w/ Moi Martinez which was nice! We ran to a dirt track in south Eugene that I think I’ll workout at some point because I thought it was pretty solid for tempos. The strides felt pretty good, my body is definitely still remembering how to run fast which is good. Can’t wait to see where I’m at with a cross country race in less than 2 weeks!
w/ Ian Twyman and Nick!

Alex  Helmuth and I planned on going to Dorris but he wimped out on the singular hill so we ended up just doing Mill Race. It ended up working out really well though and I’m always surprised at how many cool places I can run to from my front door!

My right ankle is a little achy and my right adductor is flared up a little, I think both were from the pothole that I hit with 400m to go. Should be better in a few days but I’m definitely a tad banged up from the race. I felt much better after the run than before so it was definitely a good idea! I just stayed on the track to be safe and enjoy the sunset.

Allegedly this was an 8k but a lot of people were getting 5.08 to 5.09. Either way I’m very happy with the race! It was a little lumpy at times and there were probably 3-6 times where I stepped on a pothole and nearly fell. Most notably with 400 to go on the second to last turn I hit a big one and nearly fell but I definitely can’t blame the loss on that, Bradley ran great and had more in the mental tank than me today. I settled in the first 6k and tried to synch the pace down the last 2k which easily dropped everyone except for Bradley. Again I’m very happy with this race, somewhat of a rust buster to learn how hard cross country is and how far I still have to go!

4x100m spikes strides! 8k cross race in Salem tomorrow should be awesome! I spiked up for the strides today and felt dangerously good. Thanks to Alex  Helmuth for doing a lil runners to you mark and bang for one of my strides 🥹
I felt okay on the run but @music really made it go by quicker so thanks to him for coming out! It was actually a little chilly, seemed like there was some wind chill.

Description: w/ Moi Martinez, Josh Park, and Mesty. Not much to report here, I felt pretty solid and had some great company! I had to whip out some of my winter clothes that haven’t seen the light of day in some time and also my headlamp.
Solid MLR this morning after PT. Ended up running into Alex Ostberg which made the run better! The last few miles definitely felt like junk miles but that’s okay.

5:10, 5:07, 5:09, 5:09, 5:02; 32.1, 33.3, 33.9, 32.9, 32.2, 32.0, 32.4, 32.2. Quite the group today! Probably too many features to @ but thank y'all for coming out. The 1600s all felt very comfortable but definitely went out a little hard on the last one. I was trying to focus on 5k pace for the 200s but today 32-33 just felt faster than 5k pace for whatever reason. Overall it was a perfect morning in terms of weather and company so I can't ask for much more! Got a massage afterwards and I'm starting to try chocolate milk + L-glutamine + BCAAs for recovery. I've never been a big supplement guy but I'm excited to give it a try. I only had to lead the last rep and a few of the 200s so I feel like I saved a lot of energy today.
4 x 100m track strides. The run with Alex  Helmuth went great since we didn’t have to stop very many times. The strides felt really solid but they had me pretty out of breath to be honest.

Ran before the sun came out w/ Alex  Helmuth this morning. It was a little dark to start but the weather was perfect and the run flew by despite running the Amazon loop which notoriously seems to take forever.
This was the perfect effort and flew by! It was a little rainy to start but after a mile or two it slowed down and the weather was awesome for a long run.
This felt LONG!

w/ Alex  Helmuth, Moi Martinez, and Gilbert Grundy. I felt pretty solid this morning, definitely a good morning for the headlamp! We had a very funny encounter with a possum near where Gilbert encountered the bear last week. Overall a solid sleepy morning!

2:53.8, 2:57.3, 2:56.6, 2:56.5, 2:54.0, 2:56.4, 2:53.8, 2:55.3. It was cold and rainy and I ran with music the whole time so I basically couldn’t feel anything. 4:51.6; 25:48.9 (5:11.3, 5:09.5, 5:09.7, 5:09.5, 5:08.9); 4:51.0. I tested 3.7 after the tempo/before the last 1600. Amazon has become stale so I’ve been trying to find other places to run. Hopefully when I get more routes under my belt I can do those instead and then running Amazon will feel good again. I have 8 instead of 11 this week which makes a huge difference! It was a little cold but not too bad overall. I’m racing USATF Oregon champs this week which I am very excited about.
Started at home and ended at the gym. Not much to report, I still have a very acute soreness in my right quad most likely from PT exercises but other than that the body felt good!
